  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To investigate whether the composition of the gut microbiota is different in patients that
      develop delirium during critical illness as compared to patients who do not.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We plan to include an equal number of patients admitted to the ICU, that either do or don't
      develop delirium during their course of critical illness. Samples of feces/rectal swaps will
      be taken at admission and again either when the patients become CAM-ICU positive,
      alternatively after 5 days admssion/at discharge in patients that remain CAM-ICU negative.

      Samples are then sent to analyses for purification of bacterial DNA and metagenomic analysis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
